# 7. きっと一緒なら

Len: Emu...?
Emu: Your dream will never come true if you start believing that it won't...
Emu: So, don't give up...!
Rion: But... My dream's so ridiculous...
Emu: Yeah, maybe it is...
Emu: But I also think that it's really important to keep believing in your dream...!
Emu: You gotta keep believing... And keep coming up with ways to make it a reality.
Emu: Because one of them might just be the key to making it actually come true...!
Tsukasa: Emu...
Rion: Yes, I see your point...
Rion: But believing in something that I feel isn't ever going to come true is just so hard...
Emu: Oh...
Emu: I know... I understand how you feel.
Rion: You do?
Emu: For the longest time, I had a lot of trouble getting my dreams to come true and endured a lot of pain.
Emu: I sometimes thought about giving up because it seemed so much easier... Just like you, Rion.
Emu: But I had others tell me that I didn't have to give up.
Rion: You didn't have to give up...?
Emu: Not only that... They even helped come up with ways to help make my dream a reality.
Emu: And then, it actually ended up coming true!
Miku: Emu, Tsukasa, Nene and Rui all worked very hard to make the Wonder Stage a place that's full of smiles.
Len: Not to mention how everyone working at the park helped them protect Phoenix Wonderland after hearing how they wanted to make it a place where everyone smiles forever and ever!
MEIKO: And don't forget how they figured out a way to stay together while chasing after their dreams.
Rion: They did all of that...?
Rion: But I'm just...
Emu: Don't worry! I'll help you make it happen☆
Rion: What...?
Emu: Making your dream come true all by yourself is really hard, but it's a lot easier when you have others helping you, right?
Emu: By putting our heads together, we should be able to come up with a way to make it come true!
Emu: So, Rion, let's brainstorm and come up with a good idea!
Rion: Emu...
Tsukasa: Naturally, I'll be helping as well! I feel compelled to after hearing your story!
Rion: ...
Rion: Thank you very much... I really don't know what to say.
Rion: And I'm inclined to agree with you, Emu. As long as I don't give up, my dream might someday come true...
Emu: Rion...!
Rion: So, your help will be much appreciated.
Rion: Please help me figure out a way to make my dream of flying with that phoenix a reality!
Emu: Okay!
Emu: Then, let's start coming up with ways to fly with that phoenix!
Miku: Okay!
MEIKO: So, how do we make this happen?
Rin: Oh, what if we used the flying train? That could help us fly alongside that phoenix☆
KAITO: Hmm... Unfortunately, that train sort of has a mind of its own. Getting it to fly alongside that phoenix may be a bit difficult.
Len: Then, what if we got on the phoenix's back?!
Emu: What?! On its back?!
Len: Yeah! A lot of fantasy movies and stuff involve flying on the backs of big birds, right?
Luka: Oh, on the back of a big bird...? That sounds very comfy.
Nene: I mean... Is that actually possible?
Rui: Based on the size of that phoenix, a plushie like Rion should have no problem riding on its back.
Emu: Then, let's try asking it!
Robo-Nene: Asking it?
Emu: Yeah! We'll just ask, “Please let him ride on your back as you fly!”
Tsukasa: Slow down. A bird isn't going to understand what we're saying...
Tsukasa: No, wait. We've already made friends with all these plushies.
Nene: But, how are we going to talk to it if we don't know where it is?
Rion: Oh, right... That does complicate things, but I have an idea regarding that.
Emu: You do?
Rion: I've actually been collecting any records I can find of that phoenix appearing in the harbor for quite some time, and I recently made a discovery.
Rion: Whenever it does decide to visit, it always goes to its favorite spot.
Rin: So, if we go there, we'll be able to find it?!
Rion: Well, it's just one possibility...
Tsukasa: Nevertheless, our odds of finding it are certainly much better than if we just continued to stand around here!
Miku: Then, let's go!
Emu: Okay!
Emu: Alright, everyone! Let's go find that phoenix!
Tsukasa: Yes, let's!
Len: That was pretty cool.
MEIKO: Is something the matter, Len?
Len: Oh... Hehe. I was talking about Emu!
Len: I think it's really cool how she's able to turn someone's frown upside down so quickly.
Len: Which probably means she's getting closer and closer to her dream of making Phoenix Wonderland—and even the entire world—full of smiles!
MEIKO: Yes, I agree!
Emu's Voice: MEIKO! Len! We gotta hurry!
MEIKO: Oh, right. Let's get a move on!
MEIKO: We need to keep watching over Emu and the others while giving them all the support we can!
Len: Right!
